div.p:
He had the dominion, Thou sayest that I am a King;
                  Joh. 18.37.
                  For that end was I born, saith he himself.

The Greek word for vertue signifieth properly valour in war;

                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  . St. Peter then would have us to add to our faith constancy and courage, as St. Paul charged Timothy to fight the good fight of faith, 1 Tim. 6.2. and 2 Tim. 2.3. he will have him to be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus. A fit lesson for all Christians, especially for those that are of Timothy's Order; For Ministers being more aimed at by the oppositions of the Devil and the world, have more need to put on the whole armour of God, and to add to their faith, vertue and resolution.
